events.param: Looking out the window, the stars are like pinpricks in a black page.
party 0 There! There it is again!
terminal LOG 3.03: Hector says there’s a handprint on the outside of his window.
terminal LOG 1.2 Slight issue with the causalities. Serviced this morning. Vector spikes shuffled. On track.
One of your party members hears a sound like nails scratching down the inside of a pipe.
note *This page has a crude pencil drawing of one of the monsters you’ve encountered.*
medkit

note Things in this place are distorted. Sometimes I catch a glimpse of my reflection in the dark windows, and I see myself the way I want to be, shoulders broadened, and a confident gleam in my eye. Other times I see myself the way you see me. I’m starting to forget what I really look like.
party 4 Pssst... I liked THE MOON OF EZMERIAL.
terminal LOG 7.12: Causalities shuffled. On track. Vector spikes irregular. Looking into it.
terminal LOG 5.17: Patrick reported seeing something walking through the wall near here, impossible!
There are no lights, it is unclear why this space is so bright. These blank features exude an unsettling emptiness.
party 3 The stars look painted on.
note *This page has a skilled pencil drawing of the view out a window. It’s mostly black.*
party Who here has read THE MOON OF EZMERIAL?
party 0 Did you hear something?
party 1 No?
party 3 We’re on a literal adventure, right here, right now. We don’t need books.
note I miss you.

note The stars don’t seem real. They never move. It’s because they’re so far away, right? I miss you. I wish you could see me out here. I’m doing pretty good, all things considered. My fellow adventurers talk a lot when we camp for the evenings. I don’t like Edison much. Sam’s alright.
